The paper discusses graph neural networks (GNN) and their effectiveness in representing graph structured data, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the applicability of graph structured data in computer vision (cs.CV) and social networks (cs.SI), indicating that these sub-categories are also relevant. Additionally, the paper proposes a method for local interpretable model explanations, which is a topic that falls under natural language processing (cs.CL). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.CV, cs.SI, and cs.CL.
